Yes, it is possible to change available reactions on messages in a Telegram bot using the Telegraf library. 

Here's an example code snippet which shows how to use the `setMyCommands` method in Telegraf to change the available reactions on messages:

```javascript
const { Telegraf } = require('telegraf');

const bot = new Telegraf(process.env.BOT_TOKEN);

bot.command('setreactions', async (ctx) => {
  const newReactions = [
    { command: 'thumbsup', description: 'Thumbs Up 👍' },
    { command: 'heart', description: 'Heart ❤️' },
    { command: 'smile', description: 'Smiling Face 😀' },
  ];

  const result = await ctx.telegram.setMyCommands(newReactions);
  console.log(result);

  ctx.reply('New reactions have been set!');
});

bot.launch();
```

In this code, we define a new array of reactions (`newReactions`) with three different reactions, and use the `setMyCommands` method to set them as the available reactions for the bot. The `setMyCommands` method updates the bot's list of commands, which includes both text commands and reactions. 

After running this code and sending the `/setreactions` command to the bot, the available reactions in the chat will now include the three new reactions we defined.

